Chlorhexidine was developed in the UK by Imperial Chemical Industries in the early 1950s[A190474] and was introduced to the US in the 1970s.[L11572] The FDA withdrew its approval for the use of chlorhexidine gluconate topical tincture 0.5%, due to a significant number of reports concerning chemical and thermal burns associated with the use of this product.[L43942,L44027] Other formulations of chlorhexidine continue to be available.', '["R02AA05", "S03AA04", "D08AC52", "D08AC02", "S01AX09", "D09AA12", "B05CA02", "A01AB03", "S02AA09"]', '[]');
